Shared TypeScript build presets used by this package.

# read {presets/eslint} as PresetEslint

Shared ESLint presets used by this package.

# lib @openhint/transpiler

Library provides the programmatic API for the HINT ecosystem. It handles file pre-processing, variable resolution, and markdown compilation.

The parser and compiler honor the root `hint.yml` or `hint.yaml` `ignore` array for every target, cascaded HINT file, compile-time include, and run-time read reference.

# lang

TypeScript (Node.js 22+ / pure ESM). All publishable relative imports and
re-exports include the emitted `.js` extension so runtime JavaScript and
NodeNext declarations resolve identically.

# dependencies

Development:

- {PresetTypescript}
- {PresetEslint}
- vite
- node
- typescript

# rule

- The npm artifact exposes only `@openhint/transpiler`,
  `@openhint/transpiler/keywords`, and package metadata.
- Public-package behavior is verified from the packed tarball in an isolated
  consumer project, not only from workspace source.
- Never rely on implicit `index.js` lookup, directory imports, or extensionless
  ESM specifiers.
- Runtime code has no third-party dependencies.
- Do not claim browser compatibility.
